description = Use when creating or reviewing a SKILL.md, deciding whether a piece of work should be a skill at all, debugging why a skill won't activate, or looking up or saving a skill-design concept — not when naming a tool or selecting among many (that is tool-design), nor wording the instruction body itself (that is prompt-engineering), nor designing the sub-agent a skill delegates to (that is agent-architectures). Retrieve, capture, or refresh distilled skill-design knowledge on demand — authoring the Agent Skill (SKILL.md) abstraction: progressive-disclosure / three-tier token economics, the activation-trigger description, one-capability granularity, directory packaging (scripts/references/assets), instructions-body craft and degrees of freedom, skill evaluation, and the skill-vs-tool-vs-prompt-vs-sub-agent decision.
